{
  "texts": [
    "Specifically, the project's XAI techniques can be used to explain how black box ML models operate.",
    "This enables the platform to integrate black box ML models within its ML module, while at the same time explaining them via XAI techniques that are integrated into the XAI module of the platform (Figure 3).",
    "ML algorithms can be broken down into two major categories: (i) traditional ML models, which are mostly based on classical statistical algorithms, and (ii) DL, which comprises models based on artificial neural e10-12 Thanasis Papadakis et al.",
    "networks (ANNs) with many layers of \"perceptrons\" that are inspired from models of brain neuron cell operation.",
    "ML algorithms can be further divided into supervised, unsupervised, and reinforcement learning (Bonaccorso, 2017)."
  ]
}